definition: to gush/to gush out/to pour out

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)

Out of this lake, as from the white square stone in Ben Bulben, issues an unearthly troop.

to well up/to boil out/to bubble forth/to spurt

to roll over and over (of billows or clouds)
to cascade down/to flow in torrents/(fig.) outpouring (of emotions)
